SIMPLE: spark_plug
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spark plug
<hw>Spark plug</hw>. <def>In internal-combustion engines with electric
ignition, a plug, screwed into the cylinder head, connected with the
induction coil or magneto circuit on the outside, and used to produce a
spark to ignite the fuel-air mixture in the engine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sparling</ent>⟦br⟧
